He knows how to affect someone.

266
00:12:56,126 --> 00:12:59,196
Handing someone your phone unlocked is...

267
00:12:59,196 --> 00:13:02,826
- It's not easy.
- It's not easy to do at that stage.

268
00:13:02,826 --> 00:13:04,856
Anyway, it's moving fast.

269
00:13:04,856 --> 00:13:07,316
It's too fast. He is so MZ style.

270
00:13:07,316 --> 00:13:11,146
[A warm and sunny afternoon]

271
00:13:13,536 --> 00:13:15,366
[Seo Won returned to Signal House after work]

272
00:13:15,366 --> 00:13:17,566
He looks different with glasses on.

273
00:13:17,566 --> 00:13:18,596
[Rummaging]

274
00:13:18,596 --> 00:13:20,006
What?

275
00:13:22,996 --> 00:13:26,506
- He's learning to make dinner.
- He's like a mom.

276
00:13:26,506 --> 00:13:29,336
There are five to six people.

277
00:13:29,336 --> 00:13:31,526
But this is for one serving.

278
00:13:31,526 --> 00:13:33,136
Make a unit table, too.

279
00:13:33,136 --> 00:13:35,196
Is he asking AI?

280
00:13:35,196 --> 00:13:38,786
Soy sauce. Spicy chili pepper.

281
00:13:39,756 --> 00:13:41,396
What's a tablespoon?

282
00:13:41,396 --> 00:13:44,396
- A tablespoon? He's never done this.
- I know.

283
00:13:46,536 --> 00:13:49,086
[Simulating]

284
00:13:49,086 --> 00:13:52,156
I was on Baek Jong Won's YouTube.

285
00:13:52,156 --> 00:13:57,676
I watched the ingredients and
how-to part over five times.

286
00:13:57,676 --> 00:13:59,796
- I wanted to do a good job.
- He's preparing.

287
00:13:59,796 --> 00:14:02,036
- Hey, Mom.
- My Daughter, you called?

288
00:14:02,036 --> 00:14:03,346
The doenjang* stew...
(Soybean paste)

289
00:14:03,346 --> 00:14:05,636
[His cooking buddy arrived]

290
00:14:05,636 --> 00:14:08,606
So cute. She's asking her mom.

291
00:14:08,606 --> 00:14:11,716
I haven't gone shopping yet. I have to now.

292
00:14:11,716 --> 00:14:13,426
Hello.

293
00:14:13,426 --> 00:14:15,476
Okay.

294
00:14:15,476 --> 00:14:17,056
Bye.

295
00:14:17,056 --> 00:14:18,126
Hello.

296
00:14:18,126 --> 00:14:20,116
- Did you have a good day?
- Yes.

297
00:14:20,116 --> 00:14:22,776
We need to make a tasty meal today.

298
00:14:22,776 --> 00:14:25,096
I watched YouTube videos on the way.

299
00:14:25,096 --> 00:14:27,756
Me, too. I was studying.

300
00:14:27,756 --> 00:14:29,436
- Are you confident?
- I think I can do it.

301
00:14:29,436 --> 00:14:30,676
Really?

302
00:14:30,676 --> 00:14:33,046
I'm writing down the ingredients, too.

303
00:14:33,046 --> 00:14:35,016
We have to buy them.

304
00:14:35,016 --> 00:14:36,706
Here's a recipe.

305
00:14:37,486 --> 00:14:39,726
Should we leave around 5, then?

306
00:14:39,726 --> 00:14:40,766
Let's.

307
00:14:40,766 --> 00:14:43,186
- Take your time.
- At 5? Got it.

308
00:14:43,186 --> 00:14:45,146
They're going shopping.

309
00:14:52,426 --> 00:14:54,336
The weather is so nice.

310
00:14:54,336 --> 00:14:56,856
I know. It's not so cold.

311
00:14:56,856 --> 00:15:00,066
You're carrying a pen and everything.

312
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:02,116
I'm going analog.

313
00:15:03,066 --> 00:15:05,996
I actually studied for about an hour.

314
00:15:05,996 --> 00:15:07,206
Really?

315
00:15:07,206 --> 00:15:10,086
I've never done this before.

316
00:15:10,086 --> 00:15:12,606
With glasses and holding a pencil,

317
00:15:12,606 --> 00:15:14,756
you look like a model student.

318
00:15:14,756 --> 00:15:17,546
- I can't show you. I have ugly handwriting.
- Show me.

319
00:15:17,546 --> 00:15:18,886
I can't. I can't.

320
00:15:18,886 --> 00:15:21,216
- They're both cute.
- Let's get pork belly first.

321
00:15:21,216 --> 00:15:25,186
Two to three servings
are about 300 to 400 grams.

322
00:15:25,186 --> 00:15:28,746
Let's get 900 grams to a kilo to be generous.

323
00:15:28,746 --> 00:15:31,096
- We can get this.
- Sounds good.

324
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:33,526
- Do we have eggs?
- Yes, I checked.

325
00:15:33,526 --> 00:15:36,056
Soy sauce, sesame oil, pepper,
and sesame seeds.

326
00:15:36,056 --> 00:15:38,146
Soy sauce and sesame oil? Here they are.

327
00:15:38,146 --> 00:15:40,166
Shopping together is romantic.

328
00:15:40,166 --> 00:15:42,626
[Adding an ingredient at a time]

329
00:15:42,626 --> 00:15:43,946
Sesame oil.

330
00:15:43,946 --> 00:15:46,276
- We're doing great.
- Totally.

331
00:15:46,276 --> 00:15:48,346
Five, six. We have six left.

332
00:15:48,346 --> 00:15:51,166
He was in charge.

333
00:15:52,196 --> 00:15:55,336
Your handwriting... I think it's cute.

334
00:15:55,336 --> 00:15:57,366
- It's 100% pure.
- Nice, nice.

335
00:15:57,366 --> 00:15:58,986
Why are we so good today?

336
00:15:58,986 --> 00:16:01,046
I have a good feeling already.

337
00:16:01,046 --> 00:16:03,366
They seem mature.

338
00:16:03,366 --> 00:16:05,286
Good. So good.

339
00:16:05,286 --> 00:16:07,176
[Seo Won is following the plan]

340
00:16:07,176 --> 00:16:09,596
This is so good.

341
00:16:09,596 --> 00:16:13,566
It's really sweet, but that's why it's good.

342
00:16:15,256 --> 00:16:16,946
You like snacks.

343
00:16:16,946 --> 00:16:20,006
I want these chocolate cookies.

344
00:16:20,006 --> 00:16:23,926
- You have to eat them all.
- Sure. We'll be there for a month.

345
00:16:23,926 --> 00:16:25,426
Living together for a month.

346
00:16:25,426 --> 00:16:29,296
I want to cook a delicious meal
with my own hands.

347
00:16:29,296 --> 00:16:31,376
Sounds good.

348
00:16:31,376 --> 00:16:34,696
The wind is... Fix my hair, please.

349
00:16:34,696 --> 00:16:36,246
[Brushing]

350
00:16:36,246 --> 00:16:37,746
Thank you.

351
00:16:39,336 --> 00:16:41,086
Here we are.

352
00:16:42,526 --> 00:16:44,616
- I'll put it above ramen.
- Pardon?

353
00:16:44,616 --> 00:16:48,456
- I'll put the snacks above ramen.
- Sounds good.

354
00:16:48,456 --> 00:16:50,716
So cute.

355
00:16:50,716 --> 00:16:51,896
[Glancing]

356
00:16:52,536 --> 00:16:54,676
One onion and two scallions.

357
00:16:54,676 --> 00:16:56,096
Yes.

358
00:16:56,096 --> 00:16:58,186
I'm reading your handwriting.

359
00:16:59,076 --> 00:17:00,356
I'm good at it.

360
00:17:00,356 --> 00:17:02,216
I'm so sorry. Only I can read it.

361
00:17:02,216 --> 00:17:03,856
Mine is similar.

362
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:06,646
- Really?
- So similar.

363
00:17:06,646 --> 00:17:09,476
[Studying the video again]

364
00:17:11,316 --> 00:17:14,046
- He's my teacher.
- This is fun.

365
00:17:16,896 --> 00:17:19,486
[Laughing]

366
00:17:19,486 --> 00:17:21,816
[Thorough]

367
00:17:21,816 --> 00:17:24,206
Doenjang, two-thirds.

368
00:17:25,086 --> 00:17:28,816
I feel reassured
because you studied everything.

369
00:17:28,816 --> 00:17:30,726
- I feel reassured.
- About what?

370
00:17:30,726 --> 00:17:33,276
That you did your research.

371
00:17:34,286 --> 00:17:36,186
I'm embarrassed.

372
00:17:36,186 --> 00:17:37,406
[Poking]

373
00:17:37,406 --> 00:17:41,786
- Let's chop all the ingredients first.
- Sounds good.

374
00:17:41,786 --> 00:17:43,866
Should we add the whole block of tofu?

375
00:17:43,866 --> 00:17:45,996
Yes, the whole block.

376
00:17:45,996 --> 00:17:49,376
Let's make the stew first. We can let it sit.

377
00:17:49,376 --> 00:17:52,416
But we don't want the stir-fry to go cold.

378
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:55,366
- Zucchini.
- It's here.

379
00:17:55,366 --> 00:17:59,476
Split it like this first.
Hold this and do this.

380
00:18:02,256 --> 00:18:03,976
Nice.

381
00:18:04,926 --> 00:18:07,196
- Like this?
- Hold on.

382
00:18:08,466 --> 00:18:10,456
I've never done this.

383
00:18:10,456 --> 00:18:12,196
Really? It's your first time?

384
00:18:12,196 --> 00:18:14,476
- The first time in my life.
- Today?

385
00:18:14,476 --> 00:18:16,426
- Really?
- Yes.

386
00:18:16,426 --> 00:18:19,366
- Am I doing well?
- You're doing great.

387
00:18:19,366 --> 00:18:20,766
[Tap, tap]

388
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:24,326
- Look how he's holding the knife.
- He's a newbie.

389
00:18:24,326 --> 00:18:27,616
You're doing amazing. What do we do?

390
00:18:27,616 --> 00:18:29,746
We'll create something delicious.

391
00:18:29,746 --> 00:18:30,806
[Leaning over]

392
00:18:30,806 --> 00:18:32,516
I'm not sure this time.

393
00:18:32,516 --> 00:18:34,976
I can't read it this time.

394
00:18:34,976 --> 00:18:37,646
They have a nice dynamic.

395
00:18:37,646 --> 00:18:39,156
[Ding]

396
00:18:39,156 --> 00:18:42,176
[Finally heating up the stove]

397
00:18:42,176 --> 00:18:46,526
[They're making the stew]

398
00:18:46,526 --> 00:18:48,066
- Onion.
- Okay.

399
00:18:48,066 --> 00:18:50,576
[Added without spilling]

400
00:18:50,576 --> 00:18:52,436
[Proud]

401
00:18:52,436 --> 00:18:53,976
Let's add all of it.

402
00:18:53,976 --> 00:18:55,176
[Emptying]

403
00:18:55,176 --> 00:18:57,936
It looks tasty already.

404
00:18:57,936 --> 00:19:00,446
Looks like you've done this before.

405
00:19:00,446 --> 00:19:02,126
[Glancing]

406
00:19:02,126 --> 00:19:02,976
[Boiling]

407
00:19:02,976 --> 00:19:07,976
I want to get to know everyone quickly.

408
00:19:07,976 --> 00:19:10,726
But I'm a bit shy at first.

409
00:19:10,726 --> 00:19:12,806
- Yesterday?
- Yes.

410
00:19:12,806 --> 00:19:16,316
I'm shy at first when I make friends.

411
00:19:16,316 --> 00:19:19,346
I see. Really?

412
00:19:20,786 --> 00:19:22,416
Min Ju.

413
00:19:22,416 --> 00:19:24,356
[The 1:1 chat was very awkward]

414
00:19:24,356 --> 00:19:26,556
He doesn't know what to do.

415
00:19:26,556 --> 00:19:27,726
[Finally understood]

416
00:19:27,726 --> 00:19:30,026
I was a bit shy yesterday.

417
00:19:30,026 --> 00:19:32,066
I can understand that.

418
00:19:33,656 --> 00:19:35,556
- Fighting.
- It's just right.

419
00:19:35,556 --> 00:19:38,706
Honest without being overbearing.

420
00:19:40,516 --> 00:19:42,156
[Glancing]

421
00:19:45,606 --> 00:19:48,116
[Meanwhile]

422
00:19:48,116 --> 00:19:49,276
[Yu Gyeong is coming home]

423
00:19:49,276 --> 00:19:51,886
Yu Gyeong is back.

424
00:20:03,166 --> 00:20:05,496
- Hello.
- Hello.

425
00:20:05,496 --> 00:20:08,096
- Wow, did you buy all this?
- Yes.

426
00:20:08,096 --> 00:20:10,496
We went grocery shopping together.

427
00:20:11,366 --> 00:20:12,866
What's this?

428
00:20:12,866 --> 00:20:15,716
It's Seo Won's documents.

429
00:20:15,716 --> 00:20:17,956
- Hungry?
- We'll make you a proper dinner.

430
00:20:17,956 --> 00:20:19,906
- Really?
- I'm his assistant.

431
00:20:19,906 --> 00:20:21,796
You're the best.

432
00:20:21,796 --> 00:20:24,166
- You didn't eat, right?
- No.

433
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:26,526
Go rest. You don't have to be here.

434
00:20:26,526 --> 00:20:28,696
We just started. It'll take a while.

435
00:20:28,696 --> 00:20:30,986
Okay.

436
00:20:30,986 --> 00:20:32,476
[Staring]

437
00:20:32,476 --> 00:20:35,876
He thinks everyone is like him,
coming uninvited?

438
00:20:35,876 --> 00:20:39,476
- She wasn't planning to.
- But you did yesterday.

439
00:20:39,476 --> 00:20:40,766
[Turning around]

440
00:20:43,156 --> 00:20:45,026
[Tasting]

441
00:20:45,026 --> 00:20:46,116
[Tasting]

442
00:20:47,026 --> 00:20:49,486
- It tastes like doenjang stew.
- Why is it so good?

443
00:20:49,486 --> 00:20:50,716
It's not bad.

444
00:20:50,716 --> 00:20:52,516
It's delicious.

445
00:20:52,516 --> 00:20:55,256
- Should we add more garlic?
- A little more?

446
00:20:55,256 --> 00:20:57,486
Let's add a little more garlic.

447
00:20:57,486 --> 00:20:59,316
[Yum]

448
00:20:59,316 --> 00:21:01,396
[Impressed look]

449
00:21:01,396 --> 00:21:04,696
- I need to eat it with rice now.
- Right?

450
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:08,676
But let's add a little MSG.

451
00:21:08,676 --> 00:21:10,746
That will make it restaurant-quality.

452
00:21:10,746 --> 00:21:14,246
But you don't have to. It tastes healthy.

453
00:21:14,246 --> 00:21:15,536
The savory taste?

454
00:21:15,536 --> 00:21:18,136
- Where is it?
- Right here.

455
00:21:18,136 --> 00:21:20,996
I looked for it in advance.

456
00:21:20,996 --> 00:21:24,246
I just want to surprise them a bit.

457
00:21:24,246 --> 00:21:25,756
Okay, okay.

458
00:21:25,756 --> 00:21:27,596
- It's tasty.
- Tasty, right?

459
00:21:27,596 --> 00:21:30,336
Okay. Done for real.

460
00:21:30,336 --> 00:21:33,056
Seong Min said he'll be home late.

461
00:21:33,056 --> 00:21:36,086
Stir-fried pork is best with doenjang stew.

462
00:21:38,896 --> 00:21:41,606
- They get along so well.
- I sliced scallions.

463
00:21:41,606 --> 00:21:43,446
Not bad, right? Right?

464
00:21:43,446 --> 00:21:45,956
We can add more gochujang and syrup.

465
00:21:45,956 --> 00:21:48,006
Sounds good. This much?

466
00:21:48,006 --> 00:21:50,816
[Tossing]

467
00:21:52,716 --> 00:21:54,866
[Taking a bite]

468
00:21:54,866 --> 00:21:57,226
[Making that face again]

469
00:21:57,226 --> 00:21:59,086
Try it quickly.

470
00:21:59,086 --> 00:22:00,916
It's crazy.

471
00:22:03,396 --> 00:22:05,196
- The gochujang is key.
- It is.

472
00:22:05,196 --> 00:22:07,716
- I love it. Done.
- Seasoned perfectly!

473
00:22:07,716 --> 00:22:09,796
How nice.

474
00:22:11,346 --> 00:22:13,386
Looks tasty.

475
00:22:16,816 --> 00:22:18,116
Five people...

476
00:22:18,116 --> 00:22:20,676
- No, it's four people.
- Four.

477
00:22:24,366 --> 00:22:26,296
[Wu Yeol is home, too]

478
00:22:26,296 --> 00:22:28,306
Is he back alone?

479
00:22:28,306 --> 00:22:30,216
- You're back.
- I'm back.

480
00:22:30,216 --> 00:22:31,876
Let's eat quickly.

481
00:22:31,876 --> 00:22:33,606
Smells good.

482
00:22:33,606 --> 00:22:35,436
- Daebak.
- Daebak.

483
00:22:35,436 --> 00:22:37,736
[Everyone's coming over because of the smell]

484
00:22:37,736 --> 00:22:39,626
Looks tasty, right?

485
00:22:40,756 --> 00:22:44,096
- I'm satisfied.
- Sit down, customers.

486
00:22:44,096 --> 00:22:47,796
- You worked hard yesterday.
- I'll eat two bowls of rice.

487
00:22:47,796 --> 00:22:51,096
- It's a binge eating day.
- Two won't be enough.

488
00:22:53,116 --> 00:22:54,936
[Gyu Ri is running home]

489
00:22:54,936 --> 00:22:57,526
- Gyu Ri.
- She's running.

490
00:22:58,536 --> 00:23:00,016
[Ta-da]

491
00:23:03,296 --> 00:23:04,066
Sesame seeds.

492
00:23:05,476 --> 00:23:07,196
Almost forgot.

493
00:23:07,196 --> 00:23:09,596
- I'm home.
- Hello, Gyu Ri.

494
00:23:09,596 --> 00:23:11,366
How's it going?

495
00:23:11,366 --> 00:23:13,386
- So cold.
- Isn't it?

496
00:23:13,386 --> 00:23:15,596
Hello.

497
00:23:15,596 --> 00:23:18,816
- Let's eat. We were about to start.
- We were.

498
00:23:18,816 --> 00:23:20,376
Wow, daebak.

499
00:23:20,376 --> 00:23:22,456
Thank you. You did an amazing job.

500
00:23:22,456 --> 00:23:23,506
Right?

501
00:23:23,506 --> 00:23:25,586
Seo Won and I...

502
00:23:25,586 --> 00:23:27,416
I'll fix myself up real quick.

503
00:23:27,416 --> 00:23:29,276
- Go ahead.
- Be right back.

504
00:23:29,276 --> 00:23:30,856
You passed this round.

505
00:23:30,856 --> 00:23:32,246
Thank you.

506
00:23:32,246 --> 00:23:34,916
I'm so hungry tonight.

507
00:23:34,916 --> 00:23:36,066
I'm so happy.

508
00:23:36,066 --> 00:23:39,826
[Gathering at the table after work]

509
00:23:41,366 --> 00:23:42,856
[Yum]

510
00:23:45,156 --> 00:23:47,036
[Nervous for some reason]

511
00:23:47,036 --> 00:23:48,696
What do you think?

512
00:23:50,966 --> 00:23:52,456
[Excited]

513
00:23:53,166 --> 00:23:54,616
[Nodding]

514
00:23:54,616 --> 00:23:56,296
Is it good?

515
00:23:56,296 --> 00:23:58,676
- You're good.
- It's so good.

516
00:23:58,676 --> 00:24:01,766
- Good.
- You did a great job.

517
00:24:04,926 --> 00:24:06,246
It's so good.

518
00:24:06,246 --> 00:24:07,816
The rice is fresh.

519
00:24:07,816 --> 00:24:09,646
It's from yesterday.

520
00:24:09,646 --> 00:24:12,256
[Cracking up]

521
00:24:12,256 --> 00:24:13,796
[Getting more]

522
00:24:16,816 --> 00:24:18,096
Gosh.

523
00:24:18,096 --> 00:24:20,276
What? What? Who's he smiling at?

524
00:24:20,276 --> 00:24:22,326
[Much better than yesterday's meal]

525
00:24:22,326 --> 00:24:25,366
- It's restaurant-quality, right?
- Yes.

526
00:24:26,766 --> 00:24:29,056
The soup is good.

527
00:24:31,826 --> 00:24:34,076
Seo Won never cooked before.

528
00:24:34,076 --> 00:24:36,376
But he was so skillful.

529
00:24:36,376 --> 00:24:39,826
It's your first time cooking? It's delicious.

530
00:24:39,826 --> 00:24:41,456
Really.

531
00:24:42,666 --> 00:24:45,006
Seong Min is home.

532
00:24:45,006 --> 00:24:48,006
- What?
- What's he bringing?

533
00:24:48,006 --> 00:24:50,046
Haven't you had dinner yet?

