1569
01:16:11,296 --> 01:16:13,266
You went, "ding" with your head?

1570
01:16:14,896 --> 01:16:16,846
Gosh, he's clumsy.

1571
01:16:16,846 --> 01:16:18,476
[Fainting]

1572
01:16:19,836 --> 01:16:20,846
[Embarrassed]

1573
01:16:21,856 --> 01:16:24,096
It was louder than a bell ringing.

1574
01:16:25,096 --> 01:16:27,776
Are you feeling okay now?

1575
01:16:27,776 --> 01:16:31,096
I got even dizzier.

1576
01:16:31,986 --> 01:16:34,686
[While feeling dizzy]

1577
01:16:34,686 --> 01:16:37,536
[Someone is approaching them]

1578
01:16:37,536 --> 01:16:39,946
Curious. So curious.

1579
01:16:39,946 --> 01:16:42,056
[Who is this man?]

1580
01:16:42,056 --> 01:16:44,666
He seems masculine.

1581
01:16:48,196 --> 01:16:50,626
Yes. He's got the noir vibe.

1582
01:16:50,626 --> 01:16:51,896
[Blushing]

1583
01:16:51,896 --> 01:16:54,476
- She's turning red.
- What's this?

1584
01:16:55,306 --> 01:16:57,786
Could we have water, please?

1585
01:16:57,786 --> 01:16:59,556
Water, please.

1586
01:17:01,256 --> 01:17:03,286
Is my face very red?

1587
01:17:03,286 --> 01:17:05,326
You're a little red.

1588
01:17:06,166 --> 01:17:08,136
- Did you drink some?
- Yes.

1589
01:17:08,136 --> 01:17:12,396
She can't digest alcohol.

1590
01:17:12,396 --> 01:17:13,906
- Drink water.
- Okay.

1591
01:17:13,906 --> 01:17:15,676
I wanted to drink it.

1592
01:17:15,676 --> 01:17:17,716
- He's caring for her.
- Did you take a sip?

1593
01:17:17,716 --> 01:17:20,836
No, I took a few sips.

1594
01:17:20,836 --> 01:17:23,796
[Hot]

1595
01:17:23,796 --> 01:17:26,896
- I wonder how everyone travels.
- I was about to bring that up.

1596
01:17:26,896 --> 01:17:31,106
About where you've been and how you travel.

1597
01:17:31,106 --> 01:17:32,896
I'm curious. Tell us first.

1598
01:17:32,896 --> 01:17:39,396
Me? I like being more relaxed these days.

1599
01:17:39,396 --> 01:17:45,636
Rather than waking up early
to visit places...

1600
01:17:45,636 --> 01:17:48,486
Here he comes. Here he comes.

1601
01:17:48,486 --> 01:17:50,576
Sokcho and Yangyang.

1602
01:17:50,576 --> 01:17:54,296
You must go to Wonju Terminal often.

1603
01:17:54,296 --> 01:17:57,456
[Someone is entering while they're relaxing]

1604
01:17:59,016 --> 01:18:02,816
- Near Dongdaegu Station.
- Dongdaegu?

1605
01:18:03,706 --> 01:18:04,766
[Shocked]

1606
01:18:07,166 --> 01:18:08,896
- So handsome.
- He's so handsome.

1607
01:18:08,896 --> 01:18:12,396
Looks like he's from abroad.
His brow bones are prominent.

1608
01:18:12,396 --> 01:18:15,356
- Doesn't he look like a bodyguard?
- I know. So cool.

1609
01:18:15,356 --> 01:18:19,286
[The atmosphere suddenly changed]

1610
01:18:21,056 --> 01:18:23,006
Are you new?

1611
01:18:23,006 --> 01:18:25,996
I was told to come here.

1612
01:18:25,996 --> 01:18:27,746
[The tenants don't know what to do]

1613
01:18:27,746 --> 01:18:31,346
We got a newcomer just like this.

1614
01:18:31,346 --> 01:18:33,646
Could you put another place setting?

1615
01:18:33,646 --> 01:18:35,406
He's a real man.

1616
01:18:37,526 --> 01:18:38,976
[Flustered]

1617
01:18:38,976 --> 01:18:40,366
I don't know what to do.

1618
01:18:40,366 --> 01:18:43,586
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

1619
01:18:45,496 --> 01:18:47,936
- I'm surprised.
- So sudden.

1620
01:18:47,936 --> 01:18:49,666
Have a seat.

1621
01:18:50,856 --> 01:18:53,226
Would you like white or red wine?

1622
01:18:53,226 --> 01:18:55,656
I want red.

1623
01:18:55,656 --> 01:18:57,466
[Self-conscious]

1624
01:18:59,106 --> 01:19:01,326
Today was Day 2, right?

1625
01:19:01,326 --> 01:19:04,406
It's about to turn Day 3 in two minutes.

1626
01:19:04,406 --> 01:19:06,676
Everyone is looking at him.

1627
01:19:07,586 --> 01:19:12,506
[Feeling guarded]

1628
01:19:12,506 --> 01:19:14,456
Feel free to sit here.

1629
01:19:18,196 --> 01:19:22,246
- Hello.
- Welcome.

1630
01:19:27,346 --> 01:19:28,746
[Ignoring eye contact]

1631
01:19:28,746 --> 01:19:31,876
Should we introduce ourselves first?

1632
01:19:31,876 --> 01:19:35,736
Only reveal the names at first,
following the rule.

1633
01:19:35,736 --> 01:19:37,556
We'll tell you our names.

1634
01:19:37,556 --> 01:19:39,916
I'm Kim Seo Won.

1635
01:19:39,916 --> 01:19:41,856
Oh, okay.

1636
01:19:41,856 --> 01:19:43,466
I'm Kim Seong Min.

1637
01:19:43,466 --> 01:19:45,316
I'm Park Wu Yeol.

1638
01:19:45,316 --> 01:19:47,366
I'm Kang Yu Gyeong.

1639
01:19:47,366 --> 01:19:49,676
I'm Kim Min Ju.

1640
01:19:49,676 --> 01:19:52,206
I'm Jeong Gyu Ri.

1641
01:19:52,206 --> 01:19:53,716
- Ri?
- Jeong Gyu Ri.

1642
01:19:53,716 --> 01:19:56,806
- Ri?
- Yes, Gyu Ri.

1643
01:19:56,806 --> 01:19:58,696
I'm Jeong Jun Hyeon.

1644
01:19:58,696 --> 01:20:00,076
Jun Hyeon.

1645
01:20:00,076 --> 01:20:02,226
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1646
01:20:03,546 --> 01:20:04,546
Nice to meet you.

1647
01:20:04,546 --> 01:20:07,406
[Clanking glasses for the newcomer]

1648
01:20:14,996 --> 01:20:18,146
[Exchanging eye contact]

1649
01:20:18,146 --> 01:20:20,176
- What's that?
- Is she reassuring him?

1650
01:20:20,176 --> 01:20:22,326
He's looking at them.

1651
01:20:22,326 --> 01:20:26,426
How should I say? It was unexpected.

1652
01:20:26,426 --> 01:20:28,286
At this late hour?

1653
01:20:28,286 --> 01:20:29,806
- I know.
- So casually.

1654
01:20:29,806 --> 01:20:31,696
Did you check out the house?

1655
01:20:31,696 --> 01:20:34,706
- I was just there.
- You dropped off your stuff?

1656
01:20:35,496 --> 01:20:39,096
There are two rooms for men.

1657
01:20:39,096 --> 01:20:41,526
We're sharing a room.

1658
01:20:41,526 --> 01:20:44,296
You'll probably share a room with Wu Yeol.

1659
01:20:45,896 --> 01:20:48,746
- Have you eaten?
- Yes.

1660
01:20:48,746 --> 01:20:50,976
- We had stir-fried pork and...
- Korean?

1661
01:20:50,976 --> 01:20:53,356
we made doenjang stew.

1662
01:20:53,356 --> 01:20:55,196
Are you a good cook?

1663
01:20:56,136 --> 01:20:58,026
I'm not a good cook.

1664
01:20:58,026 --> 01:21:01,566
Thank goodness. None of us...

1665
01:21:04,016 --> 01:21:07,076
Doesn't he look a bit like Son Suk Ku?

1666
01:21:07,076 --> 01:21:09,106
- Right?
- Totally.

1667
01:21:11,396 --> 01:21:12,696
I'm not sure.

1668
01:21:12,696 --> 01:21:15,226
You're like Son Suk Ku from a movie I saw.

1669
01:21:15,226 --> 01:21:16,806
"The Roundup"?

1670
01:21:16,806 --> 01:21:18,546
- No.
- No, no.

1671
01:21:18,546 --> 01:21:20,806
[Just kidding]

1672
01:21:20,806 --> 01:21:22,326
How should I say?

1673
01:21:22,326 --> 01:21:24,896
- You say no first?
- You say no first.

1674
01:21:24,896 --> 01:21:26,806
He has a villain charm.

1675
01:21:26,806 --> 01:21:30,346
We're all different.
But you're so different from us.

1676
01:21:30,346 --> 01:21:31,246
[Agree]

1677
01:21:32,146 --> 01:21:33,736
[Scanning]

1678
01:21:36,256 --> 01:21:38,436
The three of you are a bit...

1679
01:21:40,136 --> 01:21:41,456
- Feminine?
- No, no.

1680
01:21:41,456 --> 01:21:43,856
[Three feminine and one masculine man]

1681
01:21:43,856 --> 01:21:45,936
The three of you have a similar vibe.

1682
01:21:45,936 --> 01:21:49,236
You have big eyes, maybe.

1683
01:21:49,236 --> 01:21:52,216
No one has ever told me that.

1684
01:21:52,216 --> 01:21:55,606
- I have small eyes.
- Really?

1685
01:21:55,606 --> 01:21:57,836
He's looking around.

1686
01:21:58,916 --> 01:22:02,946
You all look very young, by the way.

1687
01:22:02,946 --> 01:22:04,386
[The second age reveal starts]

1688
01:22:04,386 --> 01:22:07,536
- Should we just introduce ourselves?
- Yes.

1689
01:22:07,536 --> 01:22:11,546
I'm 25 years old.
I'm working as a fashion model.

1690
01:22:11,546 --> 01:22:13,516
If you're 25...

1691
01:22:13,516 --> 01:22:15,856
I was born in 2002.

1692
01:22:15,856 --> 01:22:17,746
[Embarrassed]

1693
01:22:17,746 --> 01:22:20,556
- Yes.
- He must be older.

1694
01:22:20,556 --> 01:22:24,966
I was born in '98. I'm a doctor.

1695
01:22:24,966 --> 01:22:27,286
[Nodding]

1696
01:22:27,286 --> 01:22:30,816
I'm 25 years old.

1697
01:22:30,816 --> 01:22:33,346
- Born in '02?
- Yes, born in '02.

1698
01:22:33,346 --> 01:22:37,686
I'm Park Wu Yeol, and I work
for a marketing company.

1699
01:22:37,686 --> 01:22:39,526
Okay. Got it.

1700
01:22:39,526 --> 01:22:41,056
I was...

1701
01:22:42,736 --> 01:22:45,086
born in '04.

1702
01:22:45,086 --> 01:22:46,316
[Pause]

1703
01:22:46,316 --> 01:22:48,726
- I'm a college student.
- How old are you, then?

1704
01:22:48,726 --> 01:22:50,596
I'm 23.

1705
01:22:52,076 --> 01:22:53,526
23?

1706
01:22:53,526 --> 01:22:55,826
He must be a lot older.

1707
01:22:55,826 --> 01:22:58,846
I'm Kim Min Ju, 27 years old.

1708
01:22:58,846 --> 01:23:04,166
I'm about to start my job
as a digital marketer.

1709
01:23:04,166 --> 01:23:08,476
I was born in '98. I'm 29.

1710
01:23:09,566 --> 01:23:13,156
I'm a brand director
of a modern hanbok brand.

1711
01:23:13,156 --> 01:23:15,196
- Hanbok?
- Yes.

1712
01:23:17,216 --> 01:23:19,636
Everyone seems guarded.

1713
01:23:19,636 --> 01:23:24,396
I was born in '94.

1714
01:23:24,396 --> 01:23:26,216
They have an older man now.

1715
01:23:26,216 --> 01:23:29,056
[An older man appears]

1716
01:23:29,056 --> 01:23:32,446
And I'm a lawyer.

1717
01:23:32,446 --> 01:23:34,806
- On top of everything?
- I saw this coming.

1718
01:23:34,806 --> 01:23:37,256
- I knew you were.
- Is that an insult?

1719
01:23:37,256 --> 01:23:38,586
No, no.

1720
01:23:38,586 --> 01:23:40,986
I just got that sense right away.

1721
01:23:40,986 --> 01:23:42,616
Daebak.

1722
01:23:42,616 --> 01:23:43,856
- He's cool.
- I know.

1723
01:23:43,856 --> 01:23:46,646
He isn't just playing a lawyer?

1724
01:23:46,646 --> 01:23:48,886
[Seoul's center point, Seocho]

1725
01:23:48,886 --> 01:23:50,476
He works in Seocho.

1726
01:23:50,476 --> 01:23:52,956
I'm Jeong Jun Hyeon.

1727
01:23:52,956 --> 01:23:55,306
[Seoul Central District Court]

1728
01:23:56,906 --> 01:23:59,356
I'm a lawyer.

1729
01:24:01,496 --> 01:24:04,686
I work for a law firm in Sinsa.

1730
01:24:04,686 --> 01:24:07,276
They were all dismissed.
There was no prosecution.

1731
01:24:07,276 --> 01:24:09,356
We requested adjudication.

1732
01:24:09,356 --> 01:24:11,826
The victim stated that, too.

1733
01:24:11,826 --> 01:24:13,616
Because of the search-and-seizure warrant...

1734
01:24:13,616 --> 01:24:16,266
Do we have a search-and-seizure warrant?

1735
01:24:16,266 --> 01:24:19,956
I work with a lot of criminal cases.

1736
01:24:19,956 --> 01:24:25,686
They come with a bit of emotional pressure.

1737
01:24:25,686 --> 01:24:28,436
There have been many case inquiries.

1738
01:24:28,436 --> 01:24:30,586
He's still in custody, but...

1739
01:24:30,586 --> 01:24:35,556
I provide urgent legal advice
for entertainment businesses.

1740
01:24:35,556 --> 01:24:39,606
Starting my first year, and so far,

1741
01:24:39,606 --> 01:24:44,576
I've always been working.
I haven't had free time.

1742
01:24:44,576 --> 01:24:52,026
I tend to prefer someone
I can have fun conversations with.

1743
01:24:52,026 --> 01:24:56,366
[I'm Jeong Jun Hyeon,
and I prefer comfortable romance]

1744
01:24:56,366 --> 01:24:57,856
33 years old. A lawyer.

1745
01:24:57,856 --> 01:25:00,076
They must feel threatened.

1746
01:25:01,086 --> 01:25:03,066
Nice to meet you.

1747
01:25:03,066 --> 01:25:04,516
Nice to meet you.

1748
01:25:04,516 --> 01:25:06,846
[A new man joined them on Day 2]

1749
01:25:06,846 --> 01:25:08,616
So, after work...

1750
01:25:08,616 --> 01:25:12,396
- Yes...
- You've been doing other stuff?

1751
01:25:13,156 --> 01:25:17,306
That's why he seemed relaxed.

1752
01:25:17,306 --> 01:25:22,906
But he didn't exactly feel unapproachable.

1753
01:25:23,906 --> 01:25:28,456
I thought he could be easygoing.

1754
01:25:28,456 --> 01:25:30,476
Do you go to work tomorrow, too?

1755
01:25:30,476 --> 01:25:32,016
No, not tomorrow.

1756
01:25:32,016 --> 01:25:33,976
Do you always take weekends off?

1757
01:25:33,976 --> 01:25:36,396
Yes, I do.

1758
01:25:36,396 --> 01:25:38,876
Unless something comes up.

1759
01:25:38,876 --> 01:25:40,876
I've only seen them on TV.

1760
01:25:40,876 --> 01:25:44,456
I've never had a reason to talk to a lawyer.

1761
01:25:44,456 --> 01:25:45,826
Of course not.

1762
01:25:45,826 --> 01:25:49,986
When he asked if I was a student,
I felt small.

1763
01:25:49,986 --> 01:25:54,106
I've never talked to someone
who was born in '04.

1764
01:25:54,106 --> 01:25:58,196
- You realize we exist, right?
- Try chatting for three minutes.

1765
01:25:58,196 --> 01:26:00,886
I felt a bit of distance.

1766
01:26:01,966 --> 01:26:05,576
And he seemed so masculine.

1767
01:26:05,576 --> 01:26:08,596
I've never met someone like that.

1768
01:26:08,596 --> 01:26:12,096
- He's extraordinary.
- Would you like another red wine?

1769
01:26:12,096 --> 01:26:13,036
[Scanning]

1770
01:26:13,036 --> 01:26:14,946
- Yes, we'll have more.
- Sounds good.

1771
01:26:14,946 --> 01:26:18,096
The same kind or something different?

1772
01:26:18,096 --> 01:26:20,196
We'll try something different.

1773
01:26:20,196 --> 01:26:21,166
[Nodding]

1774
01:26:21,166 --> 01:26:23,446
Huh? Gyu Ri...

1775
01:26:23,446 --> 01:26:25,816
He ordered another bottle as soon as he came.

1776
01:26:25,816 --> 01:26:27,606
When someone serves you wine,

1777
01:26:27,606 --> 01:26:31,246
people are usually awkward like this.

1778
01:26:32,316 --> 01:26:33,616
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

1779
01:26:33,616 --> 01:26:35,766
But he wasn't like that at all.

1780
01:26:35,766 --> 01:26:37,036
He's cool.

1781
01:26:37,036 --> 01:26:42,656
I thought, "Wow, he's so masculine."

1782
01:26:43,566 --> 01:26:46,136
Everyone is falling for him.

1783
01:26:50,976 --> 01:26:54,286
They look good together. I like these two.

1784
01:26:55,366 --> 01:26:57,786
Do you have any memorable trips?

1785
01:26:57,786 --> 01:27:01,666
Trip? A memorable trip?

1786
01:27:02,776 --> 01:27:04,476
Italy?

1787
01:27:04,476 --> 01:27:06,706
Which places did you visit?

1788
01:27:06,706 --> 01:27:08,616
- In Italy?
- Yes.

1789
01:27:08,616 --> 01:27:11,556
Venice, Milan,

1790
01:27:11,556 --> 01:27:15,736
Florence, Siena, and Rome?

1791
01:27:15,736 --> 01:27:17,276
Which was your favorite?

1792
01:27:17,276 --> 01:27:20,026
- I liked Siena the most.
- Really?

1793
01:27:20,026 --> 01:27:21,536
What's it like there?

1794
01:27:21,536 --> 01:27:23,726
There's nothing to do.

1795
01:27:23,726 --> 01:27:25,866
There's one plaza. It's the countryside.

1796
01:27:25,866 --> 01:27:28,906
- You liked how peaceful it was?
- Yes.

1797
01:27:28,906 --> 01:27:32,096
I stayed there for a few months.

1798
01:27:32,096 --> 01:27:33,556
He's so cool.

1799
01:27:33,556 --> 01:27:35,476
[Staring]

1800
01:27:35,476 --> 01:27:41,176
I've been to Spain as an exchange student.

1801
01:27:41,176 --> 01:27:44,786
There's a place called Malaga.
Have you heard?

1802
01:27:44,786 --> 01:27:45,996
Malaga? Yes, I know.

1803
01:27:45,996 --> 01:27:48,446
- Have you been?
- I haven't been there.

1804
01:27:48,446 --> 01:27:51,416
It was nice living in Malaga.

1805
01:27:51,416 --> 01:27:53,436
And I've been to the Sahara Desert.

1806
01:27:53,436 --> 01:27:55,036
- That was memorable.
- It's bothering him.

1807
01:27:55,036 --> 01:27:56,326
Who did you go with?

1808
01:27:56,326 --> 01:28:01,216
I went with my college classmates.

1809
01:28:01,216 --> 01:28:03,386
The two can have a conversation.

1810
01:28:04,386 --> 01:28:06,046
It made me think a lot.

1811
01:28:06,046 --> 01:28:09,906
He's masculine and sharp.

1812
01:28:12,646 --> 01:28:14,536
I thought things could get dangerous.

1813
01:28:14,536 --> 01:28:17,366
- It could get dangerous.
- Crazy.

1814
01:28:18,316 --> 01:28:20,196
What's your MBTI?

1815
01:28:20,196 --> 01:28:21,896
- I'm...
- I?

1816
01:28:21,896 --> 01:28:24,096
- You're right.
- S.

1817
01:28:25,706 --> 01:28:27,856
No, I'm INFP.

1818
01:28:27,856 --> 01:28:30,046
He's just like you.

1819
01:28:30,046 --> 01:28:32,036
Yours is similar.

1820
01:28:32,036 --> 01:28:33,956
Are you an INFP?

1821
01:28:34,856 --> 01:28:36,116
No, I'm ISFP.

1822
01:28:36,116 --> 01:28:40,606
- Why draw a line?
- I sometimes get ISFP, too.

1823
01:28:40,606 --> 01:28:42,116
His result fluctuates.

1824
01:28:42,116 --> 01:28:44,856
I get along very well with INFPs.

1825
01:28:44,856 --> 01:28:46,096
[Suddenly confessing his love?]

1826
01:28:46,096 --> 01:28:47,996
I'm ENFP.

1827
01:28:47,996 --> 01:28:49,486
ENFP.

1828
01:28:49,486 --> 01:28:52,566
My best friend is an INFP.

1829
01:28:53,856 --> 01:28:55,916
[Smiling]

1830
01:28:55,916 --> 01:28:57,546
I love your dimples.

1831
01:28:57,546 --> 01:28:59,056
Gosh.

1832
01:28:59,986 --> 01:29:02,886
- He's so interested in you.
- He's staring at me.

1833
01:29:02,886 --> 01:29:05,996
- He loves him.
- He's like an older brother.

1834
01:29:05,996 --> 01:29:08,296
I like dark beer.

1835
01:29:08,296 --> 01:29:11,096
- You do, too?
- You're lying.

1836
01:29:11,096 --> 01:29:13,866
- Soft peaches?
- I like hard peaches.

1837
01:29:13,866 --> 01:29:16,406
- You like soft peaches?
- Yes.

1838
01:29:16,406 --> 01:29:18,996
I can give you soft peaches.

1839
01:29:20,296 --> 01:29:23,096
- Who's your roommate again?
- I...

1840
01:29:23,096 --> 01:29:28,196
[They decided to switch roommates]

1841
01:29:28,196 --> 01:29:29,576
We need to switch quickly.

1842
01:29:29,576 --> 01:29:31,576
He's attaching himself to Hyung?

1843
01:29:31,576 --> 01:29:33,396
[The women came out
to check their appearance]

1844
01:29:33,396 --> 01:29:35,436
Just the lips.

1845
01:29:35,436 --> 01:29:38,566
I don't want to go into the restroom.

1846
01:29:39,856 --> 01:29:41,836
Let me use the mirror after you're done.

1847
01:29:41,836 --> 01:29:43,106
Okay.

1848
01:29:44,076 --> 01:29:45,096
[Spraying perfume]

1849
01:29:45,096 --> 01:29:47,256
- So cute.
- Where do you live?

1850
01:29:47,256 --> 01:29:48,996
- Right now?
- Yes.

1851
01:29:48,996 --> 01:29:51,896
- I live in Dongjak-dong.
- Dongjak-dong.

1852
01:29:51,896 --> 01:29:54,486
- I live in Seocho-gu.
- Really? Where do you live?

1853
01:29:54,486 --> 01:29:58,176
I live in Banpo-dong, between
Shinnonhyeon and Nonhyeon.

1854
01:29:59,176 --> 01:30:02,076
- I've lived in Banpo, too.
- Really?

1855
01:30:02,076 --> 01:30:03,816
I went to school in Banpo.

1856
01:30:03,816 --> 01:30:06,296
You're from Banpo.

1857
01:30:06,296 --> 01:30:09,796
- I knew it.
- Which schools did he go to?

1858
01:30:10,706 --> 01:30:13,016
[Good to meet you]

1859
01:30:13,016 --> 01:30:16,076
Until I was in 12th grade.
When I was a freshman in college,

1860
01:30:16,076 --> 01:30:18,676
I decided to transfer, but I got a job.

1861
01:30:18,676 --> 01:30:19,826
[Stumble]

1862
01:30:19,826 --> 01:30:21,626
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

1863
01:30:21,626 --> 01:30:23,706
- Would you like water?
- I should've ignored it.

1864
01:30:24,526 --> 01:30:26,936
Pretend you didn't see it.

1865
01:30:32,436 --> 01:30:34,556
[Sniff, sniff]

1866
01:30:34,556 --> 01:30:35,946
Perfume.

1867
01:30:35,946 --> 01:30:39,116
- I sprayed some.
- Lancome? What is it?

1868
01:30:44,026 --> 01:30:46,296
What are they doing?

1869
01:30:46,296 --> 01:30:48,696
- That's nice.
- Right?

1870
01:30:51,346 --> 01:30:54,356
I don't like the very sweet scents.

1871
01:30:54,356 --> 01:30:56,026
It's not your first time wearing it.

1872
01:30:56,026 --> 01:30:57,856
- It is.
- Is it?

1873
01:30:57,856 --> 01:31:00,246
- I noticed a similar smell.
- Really?

1874
01:31:00,246 --> 01:31:03,996
I've wanted to ask because I liked the scent.

1875
01:31:03,996 --> 01:31:07,996
I was like, "What's this smell?"
for a moment.

1876
01:31:07,996 --> 01:31:10,616
- Do you like perfumes?
- Yes.

1877
01:31:10,616 --> 01:31:12,626
I'm interested in them.

1878
01:31:12,626 --> 01:31:15,166
What do you usually use?

1879
01:31:15,166 --> 01:31:17,036
I don't know much about it.

1880
01:31:17,036 --> 01:31:19,956
You don't have a regular one?

1881
01:31:21,726 --> 01:31:23,856
- No.
- What do you use, Wu Yeol?

1882
01:31:23,856 --> 01:31:27,386
- I use Thé Matcha.
- Thé Matcha?

1883
01:31:30,196 --> 01:31:33,076
What kind of scent do you like?

1884
01:31:33,076 --> 01:31:35,726
Gyu Ri keeps getting lured by him.

1885
01:31:35,726 --> 01:31:37,486
It's not that I like something.

1886
01:31:37,486 --> 01:31:41,446
- It's about what suits that person.
- Right.

1887
01:31:41,446 --> 01:31:46,256
When you just put it on,
I smell it like this.

1888
01:31:46,256 --> 01:31:48,106
He's doing this in front of Gyu Ri?

1889
01:31:48,106 --> 01:31:51,016
I think you can keep using it.

1890
01:31:52,856 --> 01:31:55,166
Really?

1891
01:31:55,166 --> 01:31:57,766
He's saying he likes her scent.

1892
01:31:59,866 --> 01:32:02,796
[The night with a sense of anticipation]

1893
01:32:06,476 --> 01:32:11,076
[Appearance of a new man]

1894
01:32:11,076 --> 01:32:16,556
[What kind of changes will
happen at the Signal House?]

1895
01:32:17,426 --> 01:32:19,396
He's the perfect game-changer.

1896
01:32:19,396 --> 01:32:20,796
He sure is a game-changer.

1897
01:32:20,796 --> 01:32:23,316
- Hot.
- He's really powerful.

1898
01:32:23,316 --> 01:32:27,376
He's totally different than the other three.

1899
01:32:27,376 --> 01:32:28,556
- Yes.
- So different.

1900
01:32:28,556 --> 01:32:30,106
He definitely is masculine.

1901
01:32:30,106 --> 01:32:31,916
He left an impact on men.

1902
01:32:31,916 --> 01:32:33,976
He's got the noir vibe.
He's a criminal lawyer.

1903
01:32:33,976 --> 01:32:36,136
He looks like that,

1904
01:32:36,136 --> 01:32:38,826
but I don't think he'd be that masculine.

1905
01:32:38,826 --> 01:32:42,436
The men who are very masculine-looking

1906
01:32:42,436 --> 01:32:47,196
are 10 out of 10 softies inside.

1907
01:32:47,196 --> 01:32:49,696
He joined them when they
were just getting close.

1908
01:32:49,696 --> 01:32:53,576
Men are so interesting.
They establish a hierarchy very quickly.

1909
01:32:53,576 --> 01:32:56,666
- You're right.
- Based on the age,

1910
01:32:56,666 --> 01:33:00,506
they find their place automatically.

1911
01:33:00,506 --> 01:33:02,366
Korean men are all about age.

1912
01:33:02,366 --> 01:33:04,686
But Wu Yeol doesn't like that.

1913
01:33:04,686 --> 01:33:07,496
He doesn't want to call him
"Hyung" just because he's older.

1914
01:33:07,496 --> 01:33:10,416
- He's different than Seo Won.
- They were different.

1915
01:33:10,416 --> 01:33:11,836
Seo Won is more childlike.

1916
01:33:11,836 --> 01:33:14,086
Wu Yeol had more serious expressions.

1917
01:33:14,086 --> 01:33:17,546
He suddenly came
on to Yu Gyeong more strongly.

1918
01:33:17,546 --> 01:33:18,396
[Shaking head]

1919
01:33:18,396 --> 01:33:21,186
- I think that's because of the game-changer.
- Totally.

1920
01:33:21,186 --> 01:33:23,736
He thought he should make a move this week,

1921
01:33:23,736 --> 01:33:27,056
but he's announcing himself publicly instead.

1922
01:33:27,056 --> 01:33:33,086
He doesn't want to lose
in the dominance battle.

1923
01:33:33,086 --> 01:33:38,366
And that made me realize he was 25.

1924
01:33:38,366 --> 01:33:40,696
He's smooth, but he's still 25.

1925
01:33:40,696 --> 01:33:44,646
- I thought he wasn't an easy 25.
- Me, too.

1926
01:33:44,646 --> 01:33:47,506
He actually made Jun Hyeon nervous.

1927
01:33:47,506 --> 01:33:50,246
- Right.
- Without caring that he was there,

1928
01:33:50,246 --> 01:33:53,296
he was like "Keep talking,"
and talked to Yu Gyeong.

1929
01:33:53,296 --> 01:33:56,616
Jeong Jun Hyeon might've thought,
"He might get in my way."

1930
01:33:56,616 --> 01:33:58,506
I think he made him think that.

1931
01:33:58,506 --> 01:34:02,156
I don't think Wu Yeol
was reacting to Jun Hyeon.

1932
01:34:02,156 --> 01:34:05,736
I think he reacted to Gyu Ri,
who was reacting to Jun Hyeon.

1933
01:34:05,736 --> 01:34:09,056
They were talking
about Gangneung this morning,

1934
01:34:09,056 --> 01:34:12,876
but she's suddenly talking
about Spain and Italy with him.

1935
01:34:12,876 --> 01:34:16,996
The age difference has
become more noticeable now.

1936
01:34:16,996 --> 01:34:21,596
Having that conversation with him,
she might've thought, "He sure is Oppa."

1937
01:34:21,596 --> 01:34:25,196
And Seong Min is older, but

1938
01:34:25,196 --> 01:34:27,546
he's not like, "I'm Hyung."

1939
01:34:27,546 --> 01:34:29,996
- He's more humorous.
- Right.

1940
01:34:29,996 --> 01:34:33,706
But Jun Hyeon is obviously older
without trying.

1941
01:34:33,706 --> 01:34:35,406
He looks like one, too.

1942
01:34:35,406 --> 01:34:39,066
And that provoked Yu Gyeong, too.

1943
01:34:39,066 --> 01:34:41,826
She extended her arm to him.

1944
01:34:41,826 --> 01:34:45,396
This is very... you know...

1945
01:34:45,396 --> 01:34:48,616
- "I give you my artery."
- Artery.

1946
01:34:48,616 --> 01:34:51,896
Wu Yeol versus Jun Hyeon will be fun.

1947
01:34:51,896 --> 01:34:53,816
Four versus three is different.

1948
01:34:53,816 --> 01:34:54,966
Wow.

1949
01:34:54,966 --> 01:34:56,966
This will be fun.

1950
01:34:56,966 --> 01:35:00,656
- Is this your room, Wu Yeol?
- Yes, it's been my room.

1951
01:35:02,026 --> 01:35:04,196
You probably can use this one.

1952
01:35:04,196 --> 01:35:07,586
I'm using this one. I'll evacuate quickly.

1953
01:35:08,446 --> 01:35:10,556
Do you not have much stuff?

1954
01:35:10,556 --> 01:35:13,156
I didn't bring a lot.

1955
01:35:13,156 --> 01:35:16,026
And is there anything else?

1956
01:35:17,126 --> 01:35:19,566
[Peel]

1957
01:35:19,566 --> 01:35:20,496
[Roll, roll]

1958
01:35:20,496 --> 01:35:23,486
He's a bit of a germaphobe.
Using the lint roller.

1959
01:35:23,486 --> 01:35:24,916
[Seong Min's bed]

1960
01:35:24,916 --> 01:35:27,086
He's rolling Seong Min's, too.

1961
01:35:28,086 --> 01:35:29,156
[Rolling nonstop]

1962
01:35:29,156 --> 01:35:31,686
There's so much dust in here.

1963
01:35:31,686 --> 01:35:35,846
I would've felt stressed
if I hadn't bought this.

1964
01:35:35,846 --> 01:35:38,156
I love lint rollers.

1965
01:35:38,156 --> 01:35:42,216
They have a diagonal kind,
not straight like this.

1966
01:35:42,216 --> 01:35:44,416
The diagonal kind is better.

1967
01:35:44,416 --> 01:35:46,276
The refills are diagonal kinds.

1968
01:35:46,276 --> 01:35:48,296
Seong Min is like, "What's he saying?"

1969
01:35:48,296 --> 01:35:49,916
Do you need something?

1970
01:35:49,916 --> 01:35:51,316
Yesterday...

1971
01:35:51,316 --> 01:35:53,496
- Wrote the diary?
- Not that serious, but...

1972
01:35:53,496 --> 01:35:56,576
I wanted to create a record.

1973
01:35:56,576 --> 01:35:58,366
That's nice. I should write, too.

1974
01:35:58,366 --> 01:36:01,276
- They're both cute.
- Should I use a fountain pen?

1975
01:36:01,276 --> 01:36:02,796
[A long day ended. How do these men feel?]

1976
01:36:02,796 --> 01:36:09,236
I think my feelings might change each day.

1977
01:36:09,236 --> 01:36:10,746
Keeping a diary?

1978
01:36:10,746 --> 01:36:12,376
Yes.

1979
01:36:12,376 --> 01:36:14,266
- Leaving a record?
- Yes.

1980
01:36:14,266 --> 01:36:17,296
I wrote down the ingredients to cook earlier.

1981
01:36:17,296 --> 01:36:20,496
- Oh, YouTube and stuff?
- Yes.

1982
01:36:21,616 --> 01:36:24,606
- He's so childlike in front of him.
- Lying on his stomach.

1983
01:36:24,606 --> 01:36:28,386
We revealed our occupation
and age a few hours ago.

1984
01:36:29,256 --> 01:36:32,816
I was zoning out for half an hour in shock.

1985
01:36:32,816 --> 01:36:36,066
I thought I was the youngest.

1986
01:36:36,066 --> 01:36:37,636
But you are the youngest.

1987
01:36:37,636 --> 01:36:39,456
Including women, you mean?

1988
01:36:39,456 --> 01:36:42,386
Everything was the opposite.
I was so shocked.

1989
01:36:42,386 --> 01:36:44,066
He's still in shock?

1990
01:36:44,066 --> 01:36:47,706
When I came and sat down earlier,

1991
01:36:47,706 --> 01:36:49,796
I immediately knew everyone was young.

1992
01:36:49,796 --> 01:36:53,296
- That's the first thing I thought.
- I had no idea at all.

1993
01:36:53,296 --> 01:36:56,176
It feels like everyone wants to befriend him.

1994
01:36:56,176 --> 01:36:57,486
The new guy?

1995
01:36:57,486 --> 01:37:00,636
Another close hyung. Something like that.

1996
01:37:00,636 --> 01:37:03,336
Jeong Jun Hyeon.

1997
01:37:04,706 --> 01:37:06,376
Jun Hyeon...

1998
01:37:06,376 --> 01:37:10,886
[Repeating the new tenant's name]

1999
01:37:12,016 --> 01:37:13,626
[The bell rang again tonight without fail]

2000
01:37:13,626 --> 01:37:16,196
There it is. The bell.

2001
01:37:16,196 --> 01:37:17,956
Already?

2002
01:37:17,956 --> 01:37:20,146
The time has come.

2003
01:37:20,146 --> 01:37:23,646
[The second night at Signal House]

2004
01:37:25,456 --> 01:37:28,786
It's tricky for Gyu Ri today, too.

2005
01:37:30,016 --> 01:37:30,996
[Smile]

2006
01:37:30,996 --> 01:37:33,026
Min Ju is cute.

2007
01:37:33,026 --> 01:37:36,996
[Their feelings deepened throughout the day]

2008
01:37:37,816 --> 01:37:39,646
[Biting lips]

2009
01:37:42,516 --> 01:37:45,396
This music is making my heart flutter.

2010
01:37:45,396 --> 01:37:47,586
I have no idea today.

2011
01:37:47,586 --> 01:37:50,536
[Where are their hearts
headed to after the signals?]

2012
01:37:51,166 --> 01:37:55,136
Gosh, my heart is fluttering.

2013
01:37:55,136 --> 01:37:57,426
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

2014
01:37:57,426 --> 01:37:59,336
I really have no idea.

2015
01:37:59,336 --> 01:38:01,146
It's hard today again.

2016
